The Python code utilizes matplotlib, seaborn, scipy, networkx, and sklearn to mathematically simulate and visualize the educational AI ecosystem. The core outputs include:
1.	Figure 1: Adaptive Learning Ecosystem
o	3D learning trajectories across low, medium, and high ability groups.
o	Cognitive load reduction over time modeled as $L(t) = Ae^{-bt} + C$.
o	10-year Cost-Benefit Analysis (ROI).
2.	Figure 2: AI Technology Performance Metrics
o	3D surface plots comparing NLP accuracy (AI vs. Traditional).
o	Sign Language Recognition accuracy heatmaps based on lighting and motion speed.
o	Scalability analysis of Edge AI vs. Cloud AI architectures.
3.	Figure 3: Ethical AI Framework
o	Radar charts comparing baseline vs. AI-enhanced ethical metrics.
o	Privacy-Utility Trade-off curves (Differential Privacy vs. Federated Learning).
o	Demographic bias mitigation analysis.
4.	Figure 4: Future Directions & Emerging Tech
o	Quantum computing speedup analysis.
o	Global scalability heatmaps and energy efficiency analysis.
5.	Figure 5: Synthesis & Integration Framework
o	Layered system architecture diagram.
o	Network topology graph demonstrating integration strengths (e.g., NLP + CV).
6.	Quantum-Inspired Learning Analytics (Advanced)
o	12-panel scientific dashboard demonstrating high-dimensional manifold embedding, phase space reconstruction (Lorenz attractor), and fractal analysis.
